  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lakeshore Hope and Relief Zambia. LHRZ Fishing Rig Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The current proposal would build a Kapenta fishing rig to be owned and managed by 15 HIV/AIDS positive women. The rig, an associated fish drying operation and the end marketing and sales would be split four, five, and six members, respectively. An LHRZ member will donate the labor to build and train the women on the rig operation. For the initial start-up months, an experience rig crew will go out with the LHRZ group to reinforce and further train. After the initial start-up and since most of the fishing is done at night, the project will pay for a captain for the rig for security reasons.</narrative>
  </description>
